<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 04 at 5:30AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG DEVELOPING...
Satellite imagery and surface observations indicate that areas of
fog are developing over portions of the Northern Ranchlands and
the Rio Grande Plains at this time.
The fog is reducing visibilities to between 2 and 4 miles, with
isolated pockets of dense fog reducing the visibility to one
quarter of a mile or less.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and
avoid tailgating in any fog through the next few hours.</description>
